[Desiree Masi, president of the Paraguay Society of Physicians
estimates that the number of cases is over 150 000, considerably more
than the official figures given above (per AZprensa.com at
<http://www.azprensa.com/noticias_ext.php?idreg=28197&AZPRENSA=1b147c2a4c131f5ac43098a3a774e38f>.
A comprehensive team has been assembled to address what is clearly a
massive, on-going dengue epidemic. Until effective mosquito vector
control is implemented, the epidemic will continue. It is not clear
if the public has been effectively involved in elimination of _Aedes
aegypti_ breeding sites at the household level.
ProMED-mail thanks Elaine Stevenson, epidemiologist in Melbourne,
Australia for contributing the AZprensa.com article, and for other
reports on the Paraguay dengue epidemic.
A map of Paraguay can be accessed at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/paraguay_pol98.jpg>. - Mod.TY]
