[3] Argentina - Formosa, Misiones, Salta
Date: Sun 11 Mar 2007
From: Elaine Stevenson <elaine.stevenson@yahoo.com>
Source: Diario Panorama.com (Santiago del Estero, Argentina) [trans.
Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.diariopanorama.com/diario/noticias/2007/03/11/a-2683.html>

Formosa, Misiones, and Salta are the provinces with most cases of
dengue fever, according to official data. There are another 608
suspected cases.
According to reports from the national Ministry of Health, the total
of confirmed cases nationally is 149 cases, of which only 3 were
acquired in the country, on the province of Formosa. In recent days,
the number of cases increased by 25 percent, with northern areas the
most affected.
In addition, there are 608 people undergoing studies, suspected of
being infected by the mosquito that transmits dengue [virus]. The
results will be known in the next [few] days for the given provinces.
In Formosa [Province] there are 187 [suspected] cases, with 186 in
Misiones, and 126 in Salta. In Buenos Aires Province 36 persons are
being evaluated [for dengue] as are 26 in the Federal Capital. In
Rosario, results are awaited for 4 other cases.
--
