[4] Argentina - nationwide
Date: Wed 14 Mar 2007
From: Joseph Dudley <fnjpd@uaf.edu>
Source: People's Daily online, Xinhua Agency report [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200703/14/eng20070314_357447.html>

The Argentine government has brought the outbreak of dengue fever
under control with only 38 new cases found in the last 7 days, said
the Health Ministry on Tuesday [13 Mar 2007].
Since the outbreak of the disease in Argentina 3 weeks ago, 156
people had been found infected, but none of them with the fatal
hemorrhagic variant.
Also the _Aedes aegypti_ mosquito, the spreader of the epidemic, had
not reached the capital, said the ministry, squashing recent rumors
that had worried residents here.
The Ministry said 588 people had sought medical assistance on Monday
[12 Mar 2007] because of dengue-like symptoms.
Formosa on the Paraguayan border reported 197 suspected cases, more
than any other region in Argentina. The ministry has declared
Paraguay a high-risk zone after Paraguay reported an outbreak of the
epidemic, which left 12 people dead.
--
